ters of Grand Rapids at Aquinas College. Offers spiritual formation for all faith traditions. Provides advanced formation curriculum, spiritual director training, interfaith dialogue programs, and retreats focused on spiritual growth and justice issues.", "fit_score": 7, "fit_reason": "Established Catholic formation center with professional curriculum, published programming, institutional religious community support.", "source_query": "Dominican Center spiritual formation Grand Rapids", "meta": {"import_source": "FINAL_CONSOLIDATED_ALL_WAVES.json"}}, {"org_name": "Driven Conference (Heart of a Man)", "org_type": "ministry", "website": "hoamconference.com", "city": "Folsom", "state": "CA", "summary": "2026 Men''s Conference partnership with College Park Church. Annual gathering for Christian men leadership development with prayer and worship focus.", "fit_score": 7, "fit_reason": "Active men''s conference organizer; documented giving/registration platform; focuses on men''s leadership covenant and spiritual development", "source_query": "Hunter Research", "meta": {"import_source": "FINAL_CONSOLIDATED_ALL_WAVES.json"}}, {"org_name": "Eco-Justice Ministries", "org_type": "ministry", "website": "no direct url found; guidestar profile: www.guidestar.org/profile/84-1554493", "city": null, "state": null, "summary": "Independent ecumenical agency based in Denver helping churches develop faith-based environmental justice ministries. Provides weekly ''eco-justice notes'' (2,100 subscribers), worship presentations, and builds networks supporting faith-based environmentalism.", "fit_score": 7, "fit_reason": "Established ecumenical Christian focus; organized giving through nonprofit infrastructure; documented subscriber network indicates active engagement; recognized as partner by Episcopal Church", "source_query": "Eco-Justice Ministries Christian ecumenical donations giving", "meta": {"import_source": "FINAL_CONSOLIDATED_ALL_WAVES.json"}}, {"org_name": "ELCA Campus Ministry Network", "org_type": "ministry", "website": "www.elca.org/how-we-serve/churches-and-church-leaders/young-adult-ministries", "city": null, "state": null, "summary": "Lutheran denomination''s campus ministry network building faith communities on campuses. Structured young adult support with contracted and volunteer leader model.", "fit_score": 7, "fit_reason": "Institutional giving infrastructure through denomination, campus presence, documented leadership development network", "source_query": "young adult discipleship networks faith communities support", "meta": {"import_source": "FINAL_CONSOLIDATED_ALL_WAVES.json"}}, {"org_name": "Emerge Counseling Ministries", "org_type": "ministry", "website": "emerge.org", "city": null, "state": null, "summary": "Christian counseling centered on faith, informed by psychology. Active in major giving campaigns including Global Day of Giving. Provides free counseling support for foster families.", "fit_score": 7, "fit_reason": "Participates in coordinated giving campaigns (Global Day of Giving). Demonstrates value proposition focusing on vulnerable populations (foster families). Multiple funding channels.", "source_query": "Christian therapist ministry organization support giving campaign", "meta": {"import_source": "FINAL_CONSOLIDATED_ALL_WAVES.json"}}, {"org_name": "Evangelical Theological Society Publishing", "org_type": "ministry", "website": "etsociety.org", "city": "Alexandria", "state": "VA", "summary": "Academic scholarly Christian organization publishing theological research and hosting academic conferences for evangelical scholarship.", "fit_score": 7, "fit_reason": "Professional organization with membership giving, scholarly publications, leadership roster, academic focus on Christian theology", "source_query": "Wave 2 Hunter Research", "meta": {"import_source": "FINAL_CONSOLIDATED_ALL_WAVES.json"}}, {"org_name": "Exponential (Young Church Leader Network)", "org_type": "ministry", "website": "exponential.org", "city": "Portland", "state": "OR", "summary": "Church multiplication and leadership network focused on equipping young pastors and church planters with tools, training, and community for starting and scaling gospel-centered churches.", "fit_score": 7, "fit_reason": "Partnership giving model, visible donor support for training conferences, scholarship fundraising for young pastor development programs", "source_query": "Wave 2 Hunter Research", "meta": {"import_source": "FINAL_CONSOLIDATED_ALL_WAVES.json"}}]'::jsonb)
  as x(org_name text, org_type text, website text, city text, state text,
       summary text, fit_score int, fit_reason text, source_query text, meta jsonb)),
-- Count how many existing rows (queue + pipeline) share each URL.
-- A URL on exactly one row is a person-specific page safe to dedup
-- against; a URL shared by many is a roster/platform page and must
-- NOT cause a skip, or we'd drop distinct people who list it.
existing_sites as (
  select site, count(*) as n from (
    select rtrim(lower(regexp_replace(website, '^https?://(www\.)?', '', 'i')), '/') as site
      from sales.scout_candidates where website is not null and btrim(website) <> ''
    union all
    select rtrim(lower(regexp_replace(website, '^https?://(www\.)?', '', 'i')), '/') as site
      from sales.leads where website is not null and btrim(website) <> ''
  ) w group by site)
insert into sales.scout_candidates
  (org_name, org_type, website, city, state, summary,
   fit_score, fit_reason, source_query, status, meta)
select s.org_name, s.org_type, s.website, s.city, s.state, s.summary,
       s.fit_score, s.fit_reason, s.source_query, 'pending', coalesce(s.meta, '{}'::jsonb)
from src s
where not exists (select 1 from sales.scout_candidates c
                  where lower(trim(c.org_name)) = lower(trim(s.org_name)))
  and not exists (select 1 from sales.leads l
                  where lower(trim(l.org_name)) = lower(trim(s.org_name)))
  and not exists (select 1 from existing_sites es
                  where s.website is not null and btrim(s.website) <> ''
                    and es.n = 1
                    and es.site = rtrim(lower(regexp_replace(s.website, '^https?://(www\.)?', '', 'i')), '/'));